Application schema for governance units, i.e. federal, state, and local government units (LGAs).
LGAs are known variously as Cities (C) Areas (A) Rural Cities (RC) Boroughs (B) Shires (S) Towns (T) Regional Councils (R) Municipalities/Municipal Councils (M) District Councils (DC) Regional Councils (RegC) Aboriginal Councils (AC)

-- Definition -- This class is an indicative placeholder only for a vocabulary of terms describing the type of electoral units. Users are encouraged to use the vocabulary of unit types provided by the FSDF vocabularies working group.
-- Description --
-- Examples --
- Country - State - Suburb - Locality - City
-- Definition -- An administrative area established independently to any national administrative division of territory and administered by two or more countries.

-- Definition -- Condominium administered by this administrative unit
-- Description -- NOTE Condominiums may only exist at state level and can be administered only by administrative units at the highest level of the national administrative hierarchy (i.e. countries).
-- Definition -- The administrative unit administering the condominium

-- Definition -- Description of the official status of area definition boundaries. -- Description -- The empty codeList refers to a placeholder for the different official status values of a unit, e.g., referred to by a dictionary identifier (cf. tagged value). Example values are: - historical - official - unofficial

The codeList corresponds to a register of jurisdictional unit types, indicated by the dictionary identifier (tagged value). The GovernmentUnit_TypeTerm is a specialization of the TypeTerm from the Core Definition Model. In Australia the values are: -Federal -State -Local government area, known locally as --City (C) --Area (A) --Rural City (RC) --Borough (B) --Shire (S) --Town (T) --Regional Council (R) --Municipality/Municipal Council (M) --District Council (DC) --Regional Council (RegC) --Aboriginal Council (AC)
The definition of JurisdictionalAreaDefinition extends the VersionDefinition with specific attributes related to the authoritative process underlying the definition of jurisdictional units.

the technical status of this version definition

-- Definition -- Description of the technical status of area definition boundaries. -- Description -- The empty codeList refers to a placeholder for the different technical status values of a unit, e.g., referred to by a dictionary identifier (cf. tagged value). Example values are: - edgeMatched - notEdgeMatched

-- Definition -- Unit of administration where a Government at some level has and/or exercises jurisdictional rights, for local, sub-national and national governance. -- Note -- In Australia this corresponds with federal, state|territory, and local government units (LGAs). There is a strict 3-level hierarchy.
The naming conventions for local governments vary across Australia. They are authorized by the state or territory government above them.

-- Definition -- Center for national or local administration.

UML:Comment.name: Description: Unique integer value for properties of the type used to sort properties (applies to ISO 19136:2007 encoding rule)
Values: true,false Default: false Description: Indicates whether the property is considered metadata about the instance - and not information about the phenomenon in the real world.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
/* No unit at highest level can associate units at a higher level */
inv: self.level = '1' implies self.higherLevelUnit->isEmpty() and self.loweLevelUnit->notEmpty()

/* No unit at lowest level can associate units at lower level and each lower level unit shall refer to a higher level unit/
inv: self.level = maxLevel implies self.lowerLevelUnit->isEmpty and self.higherLevelUnit->notEmpty
/* Unit type must be taken from GovernmentUnit_TypeTerm */
